description:
Many people are asking, Who is the antichrist? The Reformers all knew and agreed on the identification of the little horn of Daniel 7:8. Why is this not common knowledge anymore? What has the antichrist done to mask his identity? 
 
Find out why the Reformation’s founding principles are still as applicable today as they were in the 16th century. There are two pillars of the Reformation. The first is the centrality of Christ and His work of salvation, encapsulated in the words: Sola Gracia, Sola Fide, Solus  Christus, Soli Deo Gloria, Sola Scriptura—grace alone, faith alone, Christ alone, for the glory of God alone, the Bible alone.

But few know the other pillar of the Reformation, the identity of the Antichrist. The reformers are unanimous on the identity of this power described and defined in Daniel. You will not find one reformer that did not identify the little horn power of Bible prophecy as the Holy Roman Empire that persecuted God’s Word and His people and magnified itself against Christ.

Has Rome changed or is it still operating as a power that demotes Christ’s rightful place and sets itself up in the place of God? 

This video includes:

•        Definition of Protestantism
•        Belief of reformers concerning identity of antichrist
•        Attributes of the little horn power
•        Reformation, rediscovery of Christ and salvation, discovery of identity of Antichrist
•        Rathaus interviews
•        Reformers’ prophetic views
•        Tour of Wartburg
•        Tour of Lutherhouse at Eisenach
